(40, 23, 6, 41, 12, 38, 39, 'the chief seats in the synagogues', 'Connection of Scribes'' Behavior', 'Both passages emphasize the scribes'' desire for status and recognition, specifically their love for ''the chief seats in the synagogues'' and ''the uppermost rooms at feasts.'' This connection highlights a shared critique of their ostentatious behavior.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 6, 42, 11, 43, 54, NULL, 'Love of Uppermost Seats', 'Both passages emphasize the Pharisees'' desire for prominence, specifically their love for the uppermost seats in synagogues. This connection highlights their hypocrisy and the criticism they receive for seeking honor rather than genuine faith.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
