(40, 23, 6, 20, 25, 6, 7, 'the uppermost rooms at feasts', 'Pride and Humility in Seating', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of humility in social settings. Matthew warns against seeking the ''uppermost rooms,'' while Proverbs advises against putting oneself in the presence of ''great men.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 6, 59, 2, 1, 4, 'the chief seats in the synagogues', 'Respect and Partiality in Worship', 'Both passages emphasize the issue of favoritism based on social status. Matthew highlights the desire for prominent positions, while James warns against showing respect to the wealthy over the poor.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 6, 40, 20, 21, 21, 'the uppermost rooms at feasts', 'Desire for Prominence', 'Both passages emphasize a desire for high status, with Matthew 23:6 mentioning ''the uppermost rooms'' and ''chief seats,'' while Matthew 20:21 reflects a request for positions of honor in the kingdom. This connection highlights the theme of seeking prominence within social and spiritual contexts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 7, 43, 1, 38, 38, 'Rabbi, Rabbi', 'Connection of Titles and Respect', 'Both passages emphasize the title ''Rabbi'' as a mark of respect. In Matthew, it highlights the desire for such titles, while in John, it shows the disciples addressing Jesus with the same title.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 7, 43, 1, 49, 49, 'Rabbi, Rabbi', 'Titles of Respect in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the title ''Rabbi'' as a mark of respect. Matthew critiques the excessive desire for such titles, while John acknowledges Jesus as ''Rabbi'' in a recognition of His authority.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 7, 40, 23, 8, 8, 'Rabbi, Rabbi', 'Authority and Brotherhood in Christ', 'This connection highlights the contrast between being called ''Rabbi'' and recognizing Christ as the true Master. Both passages emphasize the importance of humility and equality among believers.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 7, 41, 9, 5, 5, 'Rabbi, Rabbi', 'Titles and Authority in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of authority and titles. In Matthew, the term ''Rabbi'' signifies a respected teacher, while in Mark, Peter addresses Jesus as ''Master,'' reflecting a similar recognition of authority.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 7, 41, 10, 51, 51, 'Rabbi, Rabbi', 'Contrast of Titles and Requests', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the titles people seek, such as ''Rabbi,'' and the humble request of the blind man for sight. Both passages emphasize the importance of genuine need over social status.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 8, 59, 3, 1, 1, 'be not ye called Rabbi', 'Authority and Leadership in Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the caution against seeking positions of authority. Matthew warns against being called ''Rabbi,'' while James advises against being ''many masters,'' highlighting the responsibility that comes with leadership.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 8, 46, 1, 12, 13, 'one is your Master, even Christ', 'Unity in Christ''s Leadership', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of unity among believers and the singular authority of Christ as their Master. Matthew warns against divisions in leadership titles, while Corinthians addresses factions within the church, affirming that Christ is not divided.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 8, 60, 5, 3, 3, 'one is your Master, even Christ', 'Leadership and Humility in Service', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of humility in leadership. Matthew 23:8 warns against seeking titles of authority, while 1 Peter 5:3 advises against lording over others, promoting a model of servanthood instead.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 8, 40, 17, 5, 5, 'one is your Master, even Christ', 'Authority of Christ', 'This connection highlights the authority of Christ as the Master in Matthew 23:8, which is affirmed by God''s declaration of Jesus as His beloved Son in Matthew 17:5. Both passages emphasize the importance of recognizing Christ''s unique role and authority among believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
