(40, 23, 9, 18, 32, 21, 22, 'call no man your father upon the earth', 'Authority and Titles', 'Both passages emphasize the rejection of human titles and authority. Matthew 23:9 warns against calling anyone ''father'' on earth, while Job 32:21-22 cautions against giving flattering titles to men. This connection highlights a theme of divine authority over human recognition.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 9, 45, 8, 14, 17, 'your Father, which is in heaven', 'Fatherhood of God', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of God as Father. Matthew highlights the singularity of God as Father, while Romans elaborates on the relationship of believers as children of God, calling Him ''Abba, Father.'' This connection highlights the intimate relationship believers have with God.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
